Detailed Description

cvmx_pcs::_mr::_status_reg

Bits [15:9] in the Status Register indicate ability to operate as per those signalling specification, when misc ctl reg MAC_PHY bit is set to MAC mode. Bits [15:9] will all, always read 1'b0, indicating that the chip cannot operate in the corresponding modes. Bit [4] RM_FLT is a don't care when the selected mode is SGMII.
